      "rationale": "Blood viscosity (3.5 mPa·s at 37°C, hematocrit 40%), density (1060 kg/m³), and rotational speed were specified from the experimental protocol with documented uncertainty bounds. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that ±5% variation in viscosity produced less than 3% change in predicted RH, supporting robustness of the input specification."
